b'GRADUATE STUDIES'
b'The MS and PhD programs in Bioengineering and Bioinformatics provide training in the research and development of systems using engineering concepts and methods that apply modern technology to problems of living systems and health care. UIC Bioengineering also participates in the prestigious NIH-supported Medical Scientist Training Program (MSTP), a competetive MD/PhD program providing 7 years of support for pursuit of MD and PhD degrees in a coordinated seamless experience with the UIC College of Medicine, home of the largest medical school in the country. Visit the MSTP Website for more details.'
b'MSTP Website'
b'I. Program Requirements'
b'A. BIOENGINEERING'
b'MS Thesis/Non-Thesis'
b'In addition to the Graduate College minimum requirements, students must meet the following program requirements: Minimum Semester Hours Required:'
b'Graduate College'
b'36 from Baccalaureate'
b'Thesis Track:'
b'At least 28 hours of coursework. At least 12 hours must be at the 500-level, excluding BIOE 595, 596, and BIOE 598. Limited credit hours in BIOE 596 (Independent Study) are allowed upon departmental approval. Students must earn at least 8 hours in BIOE 598 (Masters Thesis Research).'
b'Coursework-only :'
b'Students must earn 36 hours from coursework, with the addition that 16 of the 36 hours must be course offerings at the 500-level.'
b'Required Courses:'
b'1 hour of BIOE 595. Students without a BIOE or BME BS must take BIOE 421, 430 and 460. See MS Course Plan for more info.'
b'MS Course Plan'
b'Other Requirements:'
b'Each student must present at least one seminar (BIOE 595) \xc2\xa0prior to graduation.'
b'Comprehensive Examination:'
b'None'
b'For more information\xc2\xa0email gradbioe@uic.edu '
b'gradbioe@uic.edu'
b'PhD'
b'In addition to the Graduate College minimum requirements, students must meet the following program requirements: Minimum Semester Hours Required:'
b'Graduate College'
b'108 from Baccalaureate'
b'Coursework:'
b'Students admitted with a prior Master\xe2\x80\x99s degree in BioE or a related field must complete a minimum of 24 hours of coursework, at least 12 hours of which must be Bioengineering courses. At least 12 hours must be at the 500-level, excluding BIOE 595, 596, 599. A maximum of 4 hours of BIOE 590 may be applied toward the degree, provided credit for BIOE 590 or a similar course was not applied toward the prior MS degree.'
b'Students admitted with a Bachelor\xe2\x80\x99s degree in BioE or a related field must complete a minimum of 48 hours of coursework. At least 24 hours must be Bioengineering courses. At least 20 hours must be at the 500-level, excluding BIOE 595, 596, 599. A maximum of 4 hours of BIOE 590 may be applied toward the degree.'
b'Required Courses:'
b'1 hour of BIOE 595. Additional required courses vary by area; contact the department for the specific requirements of each area. See PhD course plan for more information.'
b'PhD course plan'
b'Comprehensive Examination:'
b'Preliminary Examination: Required'
b'Dissertation :'
b'Required. Students must earn at least 60 semester hours in BIOE 599.'
b'Other Requirements: '
b'Each student is required to present at least one\xc2\xa0seminar (BIOE 595) prior to graduation.'
b'Students must be registered during the semester of intended graduation.'
b'For more information\xc2\xa0email gradbioe@uic.edu \xc2\xa0 '
b'gradbioe@uic.edu'
