b'Graduate College'
b'108 from Baccalaureate'
b'Coursework:'
b'Students admitted with a prior Master\xe2\x80\x99s degree in BioE or a related field must complete a minimum of 24 hours of coursework, at least 12 hours of which must be Bioengineering courses. At least 12 hours must be at the 500-level, excluding BIOE 595, 596, 599. A maximum of 4 hours of BIOE 590 may be applied toward the degree, provided credit for BIOE 590 or a similar course was not applied toward the prior MS degree.'
b'Students admitted with a Bachelor\xe2\x80\x99s degree in BioE or a related field must complete a minimum of 48 hours of coursework. At least 32 hours must be Bioengineering courses. At least 20 hours must be at the 500-level, excluding BIOE 595, 596, 599. A maximum of 4 hours of BIOE 590 may be applied toward the degree.'
b'Required Courses:'
b'1 hour of BIOE 595. \xc2\xa0See PhD BIOI course plan for more information on requirements.'
b'PhD BIOI course plan'
b'Comprehensive Examination:'
b'Departmental Qualifying Examination: Required Preliminary Examination: Required'
b'Dissertation :'
b'Required. Students must earn at least 60 semester hours in BIOE 599 (PhD Thesis Research).'
b'Other Requirements: '
b'Each student is required to present at least one\xc2\xa0seminar (BIOE 595) prior to graduation.'
