b'I. How to Apply'
b'A. Admission Requirement'
b'Graduate Program'
b' Applications are considered individually by the Graduate Program Admissions Committee. A completed admissions application and transcripts of all previous undergraduate and graduate work is required. The requirements of the Office of Admissions and Records must be met in addition to the following departmental requirements Baccalaureate Field:'
b'Physical or life sciences, engineering, computer science, mathematics, biology, or pre-medicine.\xc2\xa0Required to have completed Calculus 1-3,\xc2\xa0Differential Equations, and Linear Algebra.'
b'Grade Point Average:'
b'Minimum 3.0 (A=4.0) for final 60 semester or 90 quarter hours of undergraduate study'
b'Tests Required: (ETS institution code: 1851, no department code required)'
b'GRE general, quantitative reasoning percentile rank above 50% GRE waived for applicants to the MS Bioengineering program only'
b'No subject test required'
b'Minimum English Competency Test Score:'
b'TOEFL 80, with subscores of Reading 19, Listening 17, Speaking 20, and Writing 21 (iBT Internet-based)'
b'OR'
b'IELTS 6.5, with subscores of 6.0 for all four subscores'
b'Recommendation Letters:'
b'3 required'
b'Statement of Purpose:'
b'Required (include a narrative about your preparation for graduate school and why you are a suitable candidate)'
b' B. Application Deadline The Bioengineering & Bioinformatics graduate degree program admits to the Fall term only.'
b'January 15 \xe2\x80\x93 Department application deadline'
b'December 1 \xe2\x80\x93 Recommended deadline for fellowship consideration'
